        Peloton/Concept2/NordicTrack/iFit treadmill/Bowflex Trainer/Echelon/Tempo/MYX FITNESS/Tonal/Mirror.

        Works with Bluetooth & ANT+ GPS bike computer like CooSpo/ Garmin / XOSS / Wahoo.

        Support sync with Garmin Vivoactive/Fenix/Forerunner/ Samsung Gear/Amazfit Stratos/Suunto watches.

        BLE pairing with DDPY Yoga/Wahoo Fitness/Polar Beat/Strava/Zwift/HR monitor/Elite HRV/Peloton app.

        • How to connect the heart rate sensor H6 with APP?

          1. Wet electrode area of the chest strap and adjust the length to fit your pure chest.

          2. Turn on phone Bluetooth, but searching and connect the heart rate monitor from the app. DO NOT from Bluetooth list.

        • Which some APPs compatible with CooSpo H6 heart rate monitor chest strap?

          H6 bluetooth heart rate monitor can connected and worked well with APP like Polar Beat,Wahoo,Strave,DDP Yago,peloton,HR monitor,Zwift and more.

        • How to connect the heart rate chest monitor sensor via ANT+?

          CooSpo H6 heart rate monitor support standard ANT+ protocol,Power on the sensor and find the ANT+ ID and paired. When problem about connection with ANT+ device,Please contact with the relevant equipment trader or CooSpo for help.

        • How long is the heart rate monitor normal working life?

          300 hours of battery life is based on 1-hour of exercise per day.

          As for the chest strap, it support for hand-washing about 300 times.

          * Friendly attention: Machine washing will affect the life and accuracy of the heart rate monitor belt. thank you.

        • What to do if the heart rate sensor suddenly stops working?

          1.Check the battery and try to change a new one.

          2.If battery was full, try to pull the metal shrapnel in the battery compartment a little.

          3.Find COOSPO support.

        Features & details

        Features

        • Precision Heart Rate Tracking: COOSPO H6M is equipped with an advanced HR sensor, our heart rate monitor chest strap delivers ultra-precise readings, ensuring you stay informed of your heart's every beat during intense training sessions or leisurely jogs. It's perfect for athletes seeking to optimize their training zones and monitor progress.
        • Comfortable Wear: Crafted with soft, breathable materials and an adjustable strap, our heart rate monitor ensures a secure and comfortable fit for all body types and sizes. It's lightweight and barely noticeable, allowing you to focus solely on your workout without distractions.
        • Seamless Connectivity: Effortlessly syncs with your favorite fitness apps and devices via Bluetooth or ANT+, H6M enabling seamless data transfer and real-time monitoring on your smartphone, smartwatch, or cycling computer.
        • Multi-Sport Compatibility: Perfect for runners, cyclists, and fitness enthusiasts alike, our heart rate monitor chest strap is your versatile training companion. It accurately tracks your heart rate across various sports, helping you stay in your optimal training zone and push your limits.
        • IP67 Waterproof & 400H Battery: Do Not Use For Swimming, Do Not Soake Into Water; IP67 Support Rainy Day Training & Workable In Sweat, 1-hour exercise per day, which can be used continuously for 400 hours with CR2032 changeable battery.
        • In dry winters, when the sensor is not transmitting data, try wetting the belt electrode area with more water before wearing it.

          I purchased this hoping it would connect with my Schwinn IC3 bike console... but it didn't. As a work around, I installed the CoospoRide app on my iPhone and I didn't expect that to be an issue at all... but sometimes the unit connects... and sometimes it... See more
          I purchased this hoping it would connect with my Schwinn IC3 bike console... but it didn't. As a work around, I installed the CoospoRide app on my iPhone and I didn't expect that to be an issue at all... but sometimes the unit connects... and sometimes it doesn't. If it doesn't connect, the only way I've found to get it working again is to "Unbind" the device from the app and then pair it back to the phone. It's a 30 second process, but still a pain when you need to do this every two or three days. Once working, it does great for an entire workout session, and since it's both comfortable to wear and so inexpensive I'll probably use it until it breaks; and then most likely replace with something else.
